## Instalation

To install and run the BuBooks application on your local machine, please follow these steps:
- Clone the repository to your local machine using the following command:
  - git clone <repository-url>
- Navigate to the project directory:
  - cd bubookproyect
- Install the dependencies using npm:
  - npm install
- Create a .env file in the root directory of the project and set any necessary environment variables. This may include API keys, database credentials, or other configuration settings specific to your environment.
  - npm start
- This will start the application and provide you with a local development server URL (e.g., http://localhost:3000).
- Open your web browser and visit the provided local development server URL to access the BuBooks application.

## Used technology

The application is built using the following technologies:
* React: Front-end library for building user interfaces.
* Redux: State management library for managing application data.
* Axios: For making HTTP requests to the server.


